Day - 2
What is work item, space and boards in jira
Types of work items or issues types

What’s a work item
  •	Individual pieces of work are work items
  •	Work items can vary in size depending on how your team uses them. Some work items take months to complete. Others finish in a few hours
What’s a space
  •	A space is a collection of related work items. In Jira, every work item belongs to a space
  •	Teams can use spaces differently depending on how they want to categorize and organize work
  •	Space keys are short versions of the space name that identify the work items in that space

What’s a board
  •	A board is a visualization of the work in a space. Boards have columns with work items in them
  •	The columns represent the statuses that your work, represented by work items
  •	Your entire board represents your team’s workflow, the path of statuses an work items moves through
Types of work
  •	Epic: An epic represents a large body of work that can break down into smaller chunks. Known as “parent” work items, epics contain smaller work items within them.
  •	Story: A story is a deliverable from the user's perspective. They define work items in non-technical language.
  •	Task: A task contains a detailed description of a work item, usually from your perspective.
  •	Bug: A bug is a defect or error
  •	Subtask: A subtask is the smallest piece of work.

